220
00:14:44,083 --> 00:14:47,280
Uh-huh. Sit down.

221
00:14:47,353 --> 00:14:48,786
Sit down, please?

222
00:14:48,854 --> 00:14:50,287
Please, sit down.

223
00:14:50,356 --> 00:14:53,291
- Why?
- I want to talk to you.

224
00:14:53,359 --> 00:14:55,987
- Why?
- Just sit down, please.

225
00:14:56,061 --> 00:14:57,494
Sit down!

226
00:14:57,563 --> 00:14:59,531
Will you, please?

227
00:15:03,936 --> 00:15:05,233
What?

228
00:15:05,304 --> 00:15:07,169
I know what
you're talking about.

229
00:15:07,239 --> 00:15:08,365
No, you don't.

230
00:15:08,440 --> 00:15:10,408
- I think I do.
- How can you?

231
00:15:10,476 --> 00:15:12,910
I'll tell you a story
about myself.

232
00:15:12,978 --> 00:15:14,411
Do you mind?

233
00:15:14,480 --> 00:15:17,005
I was raised
to think myself stupid.

234
00:15:17,082 --> 00:15:18,515
What do you mean?

235
00:15:18,584 --> 00:15:21,314
Just what I said.
I was brought up...

236
00:15:21,387 --> 00:15:23,617
and my earliest and
most persistent memories...

237
00:15:23,689 --> 00:15:25,919
are of being told
that I was stupid.

238
00:15:25,991 --> 00:15:27,424
"You have such intelligence.

239
00:15:27,493 --> 00:15:29,927
"Why must
you behave so stupidly?"

240
00:15:29,995 --> 00:15:31,929
Or "Can't you understand?"

241
00:15:31,997 --> 00:15:34,124
And I could not understand.

242
00:15:34,199 --> 00:15:35,359
What?

243
00:15:35,434 --> 00:15:37,766
The simplest problem
was beyond me.

244
00:15:37,836 --> 00:15:38,996
It was a mystery.

245
00:15:39,071 --> 00:15:42,529
